# POS App Store Configuration

## Worker Configuration
# Optimized for B2B POS application store
WORKER_MULTIPLIER=2
MAX_WORKERS=12

## Server Configuration
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production

## Performance Profiles:

# Production (recommended for POS App Store)
# WORKER_MULTIPLIER=2  # 2x CPUs for I/O operations
# MAX_WORKERS=12       # Conservative limit for B2B workload

# High activity periods (app launches, POS updates)
# WORKER_MULTIPLIER=3
# MAX_WORKERS=16

# Development/staging
# WORKER_MULTIPLIER=1
# MAX_WORKERS=4

## POS App Store Workload Characteristics:
# - B2B focused (developers + POS companies)
# - Multiple APIs: store-api, backoffice-api, public-api
# - APK uploads and metadata processing
# - Moderate concurrent users (not consumer-scale)
# - Integration heavy (payment systems, POS hardware)
# - Predictable traffic patterns

## Expected Concurrent Users by API:
